# Container tools — Docker, Podman, security scanning
brew "ctop" # Top-like interface for container metrics. [Ctop](https://github.com/bcicen/ctop)
brew "dive" # A tool for exploring a Docker image, layer contents, and discovering ways to shrink the size of your Docker/OCI image. [Dive](https://github.com/wagoodman/dive)
brew "docker-compose" # Define and run multi-container applications with Docker. [Docker Compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/)
brew "dockle" # Container Image Linter for Security, Helping build the Best-Practice Docker Image. [Dockle](https://github.com/goodwithtech/dockle)
brew "hadolint" # Dockerfile linter, validate inline bash, written in Haskell. [Hadolint](https://github.com/hadolint/hadolint)
brew "lazydocker" # The lazier way to manage everything docker. [Lazydocker](https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazydocker)
brew "lima" # Linux virtual machines, typically on macOS, for running containerd. [Lima](https://github.com/lima-vm/lima)
brew "podman" # Tool for managing OCI containers and pods. [Podman](https://podman.io/)
brew "podman-compose" # Docker Compose replacement for Podman. [Podman Compose](https://github.com/containers/podman-compose)
brew "reg" # Docker registry v2 command line client. [Reg](https://github.com/genuinetools/reg)
brew "skopeo" # Command line utility that performs various operations on container images and image repositories. [Skopeo](https://github.com/containers/skopeo)
brew "clair" # Static analysis for vulnerabilities in application containers (currently supports Docker). [Clair](https://github.com/quay/clair)
brew "trivy" # A simple and comprehensive vulnerability/misconfiguration scanner for containers and other artifacts. [Trivy](https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy)
